bug.short_desc: Rendering problem of Grid decorator in IE/Vista

long_desc.thetext:
There seems to be a rendering problem of the grid decorator in certain Vista installations with IE7.
Reported by Andreas Fink:
There seems to be a problem with the color gradient if I open the demos with IE 7.0.6 under Windows Vista 32bit (see attached a image). I've not tested it with another OS or Browser.

Also observed by Jim Hunter:
I see the exact same thing as he does even after I clear the cache and re-load the page. Now I must mention that I have all Aero features turned off in Vista, this may be the reason for the odd display.
I am running Vista Business 32 Bit and IE is version 7.0.6.000.16643

Andreas Fink:
Clearing the browser cache didn't help. I've all Aero effects on and the exact IE version is 7.0.6001.18000. With Firefox on Vista everything looks fine.
I have the same problem with IE7 (7.0.5730.13) on XP. With firefox everything is fine.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
